item.description:
ã€ŠWhat are the most influential people in crypto thinking right now? 1/3ã€‹

If youâ€™re curious why Iâ€™ve been able to catch so many opportunities related to Binance, maybe itâ€™s because I pay closer attention than most people to how @cz_binance thinks.

Three days ago, he had a conversation with @namdar, CEO of BNC (the largest BNB treasury company on Nasdaq). The interview was actually full of insights, but so far only about 2,500 people have watched it â€” and Iâ€™d guess maybe half of them had the patience to watch the whole thing.

This morning, when my mind was clearest, I spent 45 minutes watching it all. I know you donâ€™t have the patience, so let me summarize the points I found most interesting and valuable:
(To avoid making this too long, Iâ€™ll break it into three posts.)

Letâ€™s go.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
âœ… In the conversation, CZ spent a large portion of the time discussing stablecoins. He talked about how his perception has evolved â€” he sees stablecoins as critical infrastructure, alongside lending protocols and exchanges, forming the backbone of the BNB ecosystem.

âœ… CZ expressed respect for Tether, noting how they created enormous value with very few employees. At the same time, you can sense his lingering frustration that one of Binanceâ€™s â€œthree pillarsâ€ â€” $BUSD â€” was shut down by the Biden administration.

âœ… CZ specifically mentioned $USD1, and his comments were very positive. He believes it emerged to fill a gap in the stablecoin market, designed to meet niche needs that USDT and USDC donâ€™t cover.

He emphasized that USD1 has already seen significant growth and is being quickly adopted. You can tell that CZ leans toward supporting USD1, and he sees it as a potential cornerstone not only for the BNB ecosystem but also for the broader crypto market (important highlight!).

(I think this is one of the most valuable parts of the interview. Itâ€™s the first time Iâ€™ve seen CZ actively explain his view on USD1, instead of leaving the market to guess.

Previously, many were puzzled why Binance listed USD1 and then went quiet. Now itâ€™s clear: USD1 is very likely to fill the liquidity gap left by BUSD on BNB Chain, and its takeoff is only a matter of time. @0xDylan_ must be happy ğŸ˜†. Bullish USD1.)

âœ… CZ believes security tokenization is a huge market with real demand, but for now regulators need to issue very clear guidelines on what can and cannot be done.

âœ… On AI, CZ said it could increase human interactions by 3â€“6 orders of magnitude, with countless AI agents working behind the scenes for each individual â€” ultimately leading to a massive increase in blockchain transactions.

He even shared an interesting thought: AI could one day take his interviews, cut them into clips, add filters, post them online, and even monetize them â€” with people needing to pay to watch the remaining 2/3 (and he joked someone will probably actually do it ğŸ˜…).

He concluded by saying there are three foundational technologies that have been most important in his life: the Internet, blockchain, and artificial intelligence â€” and the last two are only just beginning.

To be continuedâ€¦





David J. Namdar:â€‚â€˜Having you guys in the ecosystem makes BNB Chain really thriving.â€™ â€“ @cz_binance

This line says it all for me and the team in @BNBNetworkCo ğŸ™

It was an honor to sit down with CZ for a wide-ranging discussion on crypto, stablecoins, RWAs, and the road ahead.

item.title: RT Paul Kohlhaas bio/acc: I'm in Seoul locked TF in in my hotel room, running our team for newest @BioProtocol launches: both achieved 20x performance...
item.description:
RTâ€‚Paul Kohlhaas bio/acc
I'm in Seoul locked TF in in my hotel room, running our team for newest @BioProtocol launches: both achieved 20x performance + science fully funded + close to $2m in volume.

I'm here for infamous Korea Blockchain Week after 24h of travel bc 2 of my flights were cancelled due to hacker attacks in Europe, then 2h of traffic jams direct to present at @DesciSeoul - then a VIP dinner by our friends at @Presto_Labs met their CEO, @MagicEden founder + http://Blockchain.com - the Korean $BIO community is really strong + there's some great local science + manufacturing we're keen on. I'm also here to unveil @dermadao who is starting directly with a real skincare product.

Today, caught up sleep for 12h to get a 75% whoop recovery. Gotta say KBW is pretty awesome, we're co-hosting an event today, had so many meeting requests but instead decided to lock in on launches.

Current market sideways and correction is good, because its made launches less frothy enabling larger investors to enter at lower valuations. Results speak for themselves:

Important PSA: dexscreener is not accurate, we're fixing DeFi routing. Easiest way is to buy via @Uniswap on @base . Below is a recap based on my own calculations at time of writing (NFA):

Performance: $BIOMEAI $1m volume in the first hour, ignition sale price was 0.21 BIO, currently trading at 4.6 BIO - that's a 21x. Team is fully funded, with token supply 10m the FDV sits at $6.6m: https://dexscreener.com/base/0x7847636614b352a7ef96e8676e4baa0f2230881b

Our second agent launch with @BiomeAI - microbiome agent is consumer facing gathering user data for precision diet & lifestyle recommendations, then later product sales (novel probiotics for instance). @kiho6redape @katbu00 @w1kke are true builders, DeSci web3/OGs, their community is buzzing + great scientists on board.

Performance: $EDMT $350k volume since launch, ignition price was 0.625 BIO, now trading at 14.3 so approx 23x, with 2m supply price is 4.4m at $2.2: https://dexscreener.com/base/0x76614f1f403c1252a7509181285d97592277d7be

@BioProtocol first IPT launch with @psy_dao @edmtcomms this one hits close to home as I'm a big fan of the utility of the substance and researcher behind it (who chooses to still be anon) + University of Florida. This is real, novel IP from one of the worlds top top psychedelic scientists. Research is fully funded + the IPT model includes a novel buyback mechanism with programmatic univ3 positions leading to buybacks of $PSY and $eDMT.

One reason for why the pricing may be similar despite the difference in volume and interest is the circulating supply in the ignition: biomeAI chose 40%. PsyDAO chose 20%. I personally think this makes a lot of sense, agents need to attract a large crowd of people globally and its simply a software system initially + token. IPTs are more specialised, already compose a RWA - the seller can decide how much to sell, they attract a smaller crowd of more specialised buy/hold investor. They're also more attractive for industry though. But historically trading volume on IPTs is low, and agents will be much more accessible to consumers long-term in my view.

If you already feel lost, within the coming days we'll have @Aubrai_ launch the first AI generated IPT ğŸ¤ª - I'll share more about @Molecule_dao IPT as an asset class ASAP. We're also trying as hard as possible to fix bugs + refine the XP system. It will get a lot better!

Thank you to our entire team @BioProtocol + co-founder @cl2pp who are working +80h weeks myself included, a big kudos to our yapper community for staying patient with XP, and all our $BIO stackers and stakers

The liquid science will flow - if we can grow the bio economy sufficiently, nothing stops us from launching with the likes of @Jiankui_He or @eboyden3 both who we're in active contact with - the key is liquidity

item.title: RT Alex Becker ğŸŠğŸ†ğŸ¥‡: New notes on my Pump streams A) For the foreseeable future, I will continue to invest all creator funds back into making ...
item.description:
RTâ€‚Alex Becker ğŸŠğŸ†ğŸ¥‡
New notes on my Pump streams

A) For the foreseeable future, I will continue to invest all creator funds back into making the streams fun and interesting. This means more game contests, giving it to chat/followers in creative ways and donation reactions etc, as I've already been doing. Every cent made so far has been spent on the streams.

My main interest is honestly dominating creator crypto content and growing the biggest following on Pump (or whatever platform adds streaming utility best). I want to use the fees to do that, versus pocketing them and bouncing like other streamers.

I don't see a point in trying to "take profits" from the stream until the concept is proven to work. I think once utility comes to these platforms, this has massive potential, and I want to be the first mover if that potential comes to fruition.

B) For the foreseeable FOREVER future, this will be my streaming coin. I strongly believe we'll see streaming coins become a long-term staple as platforms give them utility.

I'm pushing Pump as best I can to add utility for streams as soon as possible. As I've said, the current meta doesn't work because streamers are incentivized to constantly launch new streams, and viewers are incentivized to find new launches. Streamers are then incentivized to stop streaming as volume slows and their fee percentage is reduced, so viewers are double-incentivized to bounce.

This punishes people who are actually there to make content and viewers who are there to engage, while rewarding short-term stream launches and people with no real interest in viewing.

That said, if some other platform adds utility or long-term functions to stream coins, part of me streaming there would be them importing $strszn OR airdropping all the holders the new coin (a 1-to-1 switch, with no bonus coins or extra coins).

As I've stated, I'm not promising anything, and I will never manipulate the coin or do things to pump it. I am, however, clearly stating my goal: if I do stream, it's for long-term content and using the token fees to grow that content. I think this gives it a huge edge over any other place I can stream crypto content.

For example, Twitch would pay me like $300 to do a stream for 2k people. We can do a stream on Pump and make way more, and then reinvest it into making over-the-top contests and promotions.

item.title: RT BaneğŸ’¤: I miss the old crypto. Back then, it was full of addicts, weirdos, shitposters, and misfits who never quite fit into society. It was a cu...
item.description:
RTâ€‚BaneğŸ’¤
I miss the old crypto.

Back then, it was full of addicts, weirdos, shitposters, and misfits who never quite fit into society. It was a cult of people who spoke up for bad taste, who reveled in nonsense and embraced absurdity. We found a place to hide inside this giant casino, and somehowâ€”even while losing moneyâ€”it felt like we were escaping the pain of real life for a while.
I was always the least cool kid in class, but I kind of loved being surrounded by bad kids and dumb narratives.

Now everything feels too polished, too righteous, too picture-perfect. Even though you know theyâ€™re still scammers, they dress like kings and talk like angels, and it leaves you nothing to fight back with.

Has the industry actually changed at all from four years ago? It doesnâ€™t seem like it. The same startup ideas, the same product designs, the same pump-and-dumps. The only difference is, they tell us the reason we didnâ€™t make it back then is because we werenâ€™t â€œchosenâ€â€”not from tradfi, not regulatory royalty like them. And maybe they did win, for now.

So what has crypto really brought to the world? If the answer is still just gamblingâ€¦ then I hope at least this casino can have more weird voices again. More outcasts, more chaos, more color. More CULTS.

I miss the old crypto.
